    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - HEATER AND AIR CONDITIONER (HVAC) -
        Heaters - Convection Heater Fault Detection Management
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="x08290940" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Convection Heater Fault Detection Management</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The testing method for troubleshooting the electrical systems portrayed in this manual is a basic
                    voltage test. An alternative method of checking for voltage drops within a given circuit may be a
                    quicker method of identifying an exact problem.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>Problems in the heater circuits can be caused by a blown fuse, a short, an open, a faulty relay, or a
            faulty switch.
        </para>
        <figure id="f082901313" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/G082901313.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
            <caption>Convection Heater Circuit Diagram - Always Refer to the Circuit Diagram Book for Latest Circuit
                Information.
            </caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>J135 FLASHER PLATE TO HEATER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <table id="t08290948" tblwidth="pg-wide" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Convection Heater Circuit Tests</title>
            <tgroup cols="6">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.58in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.64in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.87in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="1.90in"/>
                <spanspec namest="4" nameend="6" spanname="S4T6"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="S1T6"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="3" spanname="S2T3"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Convection Heater Flow Control Valve Voltage Test</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>Check with ignition on and convection heater off.</para>
                            <note>
                                <para>Always check connectors for damage and pushed-out terminals. Also check turn
                                    signal assemblies for damage or corrosion.
                                </para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Convection heater flow control valve high to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>0 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                            <para>If voltage is present, check for short in circuit 16 BLU 22.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                            <para>While meter is still connected to the convection heater flow control valve from high
                                to ground, activate convection heater by closing the rear heater switch (C24).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Convection heater flow control valve high to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                            <para>If voltage is missing, check for blown fuse #40. Also check for open or short in
                                circuits 16 BLU 22 and 16 BLK 10.
                            </para>
                            <para>Also check for continuity in rear heater switch (C24).</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Convection heater flow control valve high to cavity 786.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                            <para>If voltage is missing, check for open or short in circuit 16 WHT 75.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Convection heater flow control valve high to cavity 787.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3" align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                            <para>If voltage is missing, check for open or short in circuit 16 WHT 23.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
